    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Worst Airport Award</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Steven Lewis article on Jan 8 editorial scores Port Authority of New York and New Jersey management of La Guardia and Kennedy airports</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>There is no reasonable defense of the two New York airports or the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey (''The Mayor Eyes the Airports,'' editorial, Jan. 8). Anyone who travels knows there are no other major metropolitan airports in the United States that look as rundown, treat customers with such disdain or are as inaccessible and poorly managed.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>There is no reasonable defense of the two New York airports or the Port Authority of New York and New Jersey (''The Mayor Eyes the Airports,'' editorial, Jan. 8). Anyone who travels knows there are no other major metropolitan airports in the United States that look as rundown, treat customers with such disdain or are as inaccessible and poorly managed.</p>
        <p>La Guardia was a mess years before Congress lifted caps on new service. Kennedy is not simply undergoing an ''ambitious $9 billion makeover''; it has looked and acted like a construction site since I was a kid on Long Island and it was called Idlewild.</p>
        <p>STEVEN LEWIS  New Paltz, N.Y., Jan. 8, 2001</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
